circumstances.circumstancesOfRecovery: The body of an African American female between the age of 12 and 23 was found in a river in Clinton County, Iowa on April 11, 1975. No clothing or jewelry were found on the body. The decedent is estimated to be between 5 feet, 2 inches and 5 feet, 4 inches in height, weight between 100 to 120 pounds, having a medium build and black hair. The decedent was noted on autopsy examination to be approximately 10 weeks pregnant. Death is estimated to have occurred sometime in early 1975.

circumstances.circumstancesOfRecovery: Law enforcement called to emergency department on 08/22/2024 to help in identification of unidentified female. Female refused to release her legal name, saying she made a new life for herself. Female gave law enforcement an alias - Julia Longfellow. Female stated she had been living in Ames for 10 years with a woman, working in exchange for room and board. Female died on 09/06/2024. This became a medical examiner case to make a positive identification.

circumstances.circumstancesOfRecovery:
Location: Yellow Banks Park along Des Moines River. 
On 6/16/2023 at approximately 1926 individuals were playing on sand bank along the Des Moines River, when they saw what they believed to be a skull. The skull was half out of the sand, so they dug it out the rest of the way, then washed it off in the water.  These individuals called 911, Polk County Sheriff Deputies a Iowa Department of Natural Resources Officer and a Polk County Medical Examiner Investigator responded to the scene.  LE and MEI conducted a search of the area where the skull was found and found no other human remains.  They skull was delivered to the Iowa Office of the State Medical Examiner for examination.

circumstances.circumstancesOfRecovery: Human skeletal remains were discovered in a roadside ditch 1/2 mile east of Correctionville, Iowa in Woodbury County on August 30, 1988.  The remains were determined to be those of a white male with an estimated age range between 30 to 60 years.  The remains were estimated to measure 5 feet and 6 inches in height.  It is also estimated that the decedent died sometime between the years 1971 and 1973.

circumstances.circumstancesOfRecovery: Human skeletal remains were found on 03/31/1986 between hay bales on a farm site in Winneshiek County, Iowa.  Examination of the skeletonized remains showed that they were those of a white male, 33-36 years of age, 5'6" to 5'9" in height, and weighed between 145 - 160 lbs.  The decedent had brown hair and a medium build.  The individual may have been traveling from Ohio to California.  It is estimated that the decedent may have died in April of the year 1985.
